

## Python in neovim

LSP navigation (`gd`, `gr`, `K`, `[d`, `]d`) works the same as any other filetype — see `dfh neovim`.

## Linting & formatting

Linting (ruff, including isort `I` rules) and formatting (`ruff_fix` + `ruff_format`) run automatically — diagnostics update live as you type, and the buffer is formatted on save. No keys needed.

## Debugging (nvim-dap)

| Key         | Action                        |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `Space+db`  | Toggle breakpoint             |
| `Space+dc`  | Continue / start debugging    |
| `Space+do`  | Step over                     |
| `Space+di`  | Step into                     |
| `Space+dO`  | Step out                      |
| `Space+dt`  | Terminate debug session       |
| `Space+du`  | Toggle debug UI                |
